    "name":  "Garden Fresh Tomato Soup",
    "instructions":  "1. Combine the tomatoes, chicken broth, garlic cloves, and onion in a stockpot over medium heat. Bring to a boil, and gently simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes to blend flavors.  \n\n2. Remove from heat and run the mixture through a food mill into a large bowl, or pan. Discard any pulp left in the food mill.  \n\n3. Melt the butter over medium heat in the now empty stockpot. Stir in the flour to make a roux by cooking, whisking constantly, until medium brown.  \n\n4. Gradually whisk in a bit of the tomato mixture to prevent lumps, then stir in the rest.  \n\n5. Season with sugar and salt to taste. Serve hot and enjoy!",
